WEBVTT

1
00:01:15.286 --> 00:01:16.458
Buddy.

2
00:01:17.421 --> 00:01:18.491
Hey.

3
00:01:20.824 --> 00:01:23.304
What's with the grin, pal?

4
00:01:25.262 --> 00:01:30.041
Mr. Castillo said I did a good job.
He even gave me an extra dollar.


5
00:01:30.267 --> 00:01:31.541
Yeah?

6
00:01:31.869 --> 00:01:36.079
So, that's your first paycheck, pal.
You never forget that.


7
00:01:37.007 --> 00:01:41.712
I told him to make it in three parts.
For you, me, and Jakey.


8
00:01:41.812 --> 00:01:42.780
Smart.

9
00:01:42.880 --> 00:01:45.249
Jakey gets the extra dollar,
'cause he's the youngest.


10
00:01:45.349 --> 00:01:47.384
Well, that he is.

11
00:01:47.484 --> 00:01:49.794
Or I could get him a new violin.

12
00:01:51.155 --> 00:01:53.524
For six bucks? I doubt it.

13
00:01:53.624 --> 00:01:55.570
But I'll tell you what.

14
00:01:56.860 --> 00:02:01.969
You give Jakey that six bucks
and I'll throw in the fiddle for free.


15
00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:06.077
Jakey'll go bananas. Bananas!

16
00:02:06.704 --> 00:02:07.944
Yeah, he will.

17
00:02:08.138 --> 00:02:09.981
Here, you want to
take her for a spin?

18
00:02:10.174 --> 00:02:11.175
Okay.

19
00:02:25.656 --> 00:02:27.966
Those kids that call you slow...

20
00:02:29.193 --> 00:02:30.194
Yeah.

21
00:02:30.828 --> 00:02:32.865
They should see you shoot, boy.

22
00:02:34.265 --> 00:02:35.801
Get that target there.

23
00:02:40.037 --> 00:02:43.507
Do you think if I keep shooting good,
that I could get a star, too?


24
00:02:44.775 --> 00:02:46.118
Sure, son.

25
00:02:46.644 --> 00:02:48.590
Then we could be partners?

26
00:02:49.780 --> 00:02:51.259
We are partners.

27
00:02:52.883 --> 00:02:55.227
But then I'd have
to shoot people, right?


28
00:02:56.120 --> 00:02:57.360
You might.

29
00:02:59.423 --> 00:03:01.198
I'm not sure I'd like that.

30
00:03:01.759 --> 00:03:06.071
Well, I don't like it, either, Buddy,
but there's a lot of bad people out there.


31
00:03:07.765 --> 00:03:10.644
Somebody's gotta stop 'em.
You know, if everybody said,


32
00:03:11.235 --> 00:03:13.112
"I'm not gonna do that job," then...

33
00:03:14.038 --> 00:03:16.109
Well, who would stop 'em?

34
00:03:21.245 --> 00:03:23.987
Man, that is some talent
you got there, kid.


35
00:03:25.149 --> 00:03:26.787
Jakey's also talented.

36
00:03:27.418 --> 00:03:29.056
You've got two talented sons.

37
00:03:30.621 --> 00:03:33.257
Well, Mr. Ashman says
he saw that talented brother of yours


38
00:03:33.357 --> 00:03:35.860
out on his property again yesterday.

39
00:03:38.495 --> 00:03:39.701
With a slingshot.

40
00:03:40.130 --> 00:03:42.032
Jakey never left the house.

41
00:03:42.132 --> 00:03:45.045
He was at home playing checkers with me
the whole afternoon.


42
00:03:46.170 --> 00:03:48.707
Buddy, why do you always
gotta protect your brother?


43
00:03:49.039 --> 00:03:51.383
'Cause he always lets me
win at checkers.


44
00:03:57.481 --> 00:04:00.655
Pop, we're gonna miss Jakey's recital.

45
00:04:01.452 --> 00:04:03.398
No, we got plenty of time.

46
00:04:46.663 --> 00:04:47.835
Jakey.

47
00:06:09.079 --> 00:06:10.956
They say the kitchen's closed.

48
00:06:11.482 --> 00:06:12.716
I can get you a coffee.

49
00:06:12.816 --> 00:06:15.057
I lost my daddy, too,
when I was a boy.

50
00:06:16.987 --> 00:06:20.196
I showed up at work. 
Just like you.

51
00:06:21.091 --> 00:06:22.468
To support the family.

52
00:06:24.361 --> 00:06:27.308
But I couldn't get my daddy
out of my head.


53
00:06:29.666 --> 00:06:31.202
How did he die?

54
00:06:33.971 --> 00:06:35.143
Somebody shoot him?

55
00:06:35.339 --> 00:06:36.613
Yes.

56
00:06:38.575 --> 00:06:39.952
A bad man.

57
00:06:41.712 --> 00:06:44.556
I met that man once, too.
In the drug store.


58
00:06:46.884 --> 00:06:49.364
He stopped and smiled at me.

59
00:06:50.187 --> 00:06:51.928
I did nothing.

60
00:06:53.457 --> 00:06:54.663
Nothing.

61
00:06:58.095 --> 00:07:01.508
And that kills me to this day.

62
00:07:01.765 --> 00:07:03.005
You know?

63
00:07:06.103 --> 00:07:07.377
Sit down, boy.

64
00:07:10.440 --> 00:07:11.510
Listen.

65
00:07:12.009 --> 00:07:16.856
That man who killed your father,
he won't get away. No, son, he won't.


66
00:07:20.117 --> 00:07:23.189
I want you to read that out.

67
00:07:27.758 --> 00:07:29.359
"Miguel Santion."

68
00:07:29.459 --> 00:07:30.733
Yes.

69
00:07:32.496 --> 00:07:34.237
You know him?

70
00:07:35.666 --> 00:07:37.646
Take a good look.

71
00:07:39.236 --> 00:07:40.806
He's the one.

72
00:07:42.472 --> 00:07:44.713
He killed your daddy.

73
00:07:45.909 --> 00:07:48.287
Now, you cannot let him get away.

74
00:07:49.379 --> 00:07:51.120
Kill him.

75
00:07:54.685 --> 00:07:56.756
- I can't.
- You can't?


76
00:07:58.355 --> 00:08:00.198
I don't know where he lives.

77
00:08:02.225 --> 00:08:04.068
You don't know where he...

78
00:08:07.197 --> 00:08:10.770
Why, I can find him for you.
That's not a...


79
00:08:11.034 --> 00:08:14.311
Look, I want you to take this.
Go ahead, son.


80
00:08:14.471 --> 00:08:16.348
Pick it up.

81
00:08:24.214 --> 00:08:25.659
That's my father's.

82
00:08:29.286 --> 00:08:31.562
Did you earn it like your daddy?

83
00:08:33.023 --> 00:08:35.094
No, I don't think you did.

84
00:08:36.393 --> 00:08:39.101
I think you got it because he died.

85
00:08:41.064 --> 00:08:44.443
I think your daddy
would want you to earn it?


86
00:08:45.168 --> 00:08:46.670
Earn this.

87
00:08:48.005 --> 00:08:52.283
You earn it and I'll pin it
on you myself.


88
00:08:54.244 --> 00:08:56.053
You understand me?

89
00:08:56.380 --> 00:08:57.723
Yeah.

90
00:08:58.148 --> 00:08:59.957
I understand.

91
00:09:46.530 --> 00:09:49.166
I'm sorry for bothering you
so late, ma'am.


92
00:09:49.266 --> 00:09:51.068
But I need to speak to Mr. Santion...

93
00:09:51.168 --> 00:09:52.579
Who the fuck are you?

94
00:09:53.370 --> 00:09:57.113
I'm Buddy. I work at the diner.

95
00:09:58.709 --> 00:10:01.451
Don't move!
Don't you fucking move, retard!


96
00:10:10.620 --> 00:10:12.293
What are you doing with my picture,
you stupid fuck?


97
00:10:13.056 --> 00:10:14.865
I was just making sure it was you.

98
00:10:31.608 --> 00:10:35.012
- Welcome to the family.
- Thank you, Mr. Hench.


99
00:10:35.112 --> 00:10:36.853
Call me Julius, son.

100
00:10:47.791 --> 00:10:50.499
- Jakey's had his supper.
- Thanks, Ignacio.


101
00:11:12.449 --> 00:11:14.793
Jakey, I ain't coming to school no more.

102
00:11:16.920 --> 00:11:18.558
I got a new job.

103
00:11:19.489 --> 00:11:21.662
So, I can take care of us.

104
00:11:25.829 --> 00:11:28.265
Tell me about the ranch.

105
00:11:28.365 --> 00:11:31.902
Well, it'll be just you and me,

106
00:11:32.002 --> 00:11:34.071
and our house on the lake.

107
00:11:34.171 --> 00:11:35.707
Are there horses?

108
00:11:36.173 --> 00:11:40.553
Are you kidding me?
What's a ranch without horses, dummy?


109
00:11:42.312 --> 00:11:47.022
I'll get you a white stallion,
with a red tanned saddle.


110
00:11:47.484 --> 00:11:48.554
All your own.

111
00:11:49.519 --> 00:11:51.157
- Swear?
- Swear.


112
00:11:52.989 --> 00:11:54.832
You just play your violin, okay?

113
00:11:57.127 --> 00:12:00.631
Ignacio said, if I play real good,

114
00:12:01.665 --> 00:12:03.542
Pop can hear it.

115
00:13:01.057 --> 00:13:03.293
They said they'd let me know.

116
00:13:03.393 --> 00:13:06.431
"Don't call us, we'll call you."

117
00:13:07.497 --> 00:13:09.166
I should've played Bach.

118
00:13:09.266 --> 00:13:11.334
But you love Paganini.

119
00:13:11.434 --> 00:13:13.470
I fell in love with you
when you played Paganini.


120
00:13:13.570 --> 00:13:15.743
Yeah, well, they didn't.

121
00:13:19.209 --> 00:13:22.247
Why don't you just bring it to the wedding?
I'll get you a ticket.


122
00:13:25.415 --> 00:13:29.488
Buddy, I can't. I'm sorry.
I told you, I just can't, okay?


123
00:13:30.053 --> 00:13:32.226
I will tell her, Buds. Bye.

124
00:13:33.223 --> 00:13:34.424
Tell her what?

125
00:13:34.524 --> 00:13:36.868
Buddy wants me to come home.

126
00:13:37.427 --> 00:13:40.601
He got us a present.
He says he can't bring it to the wedding.


127
00:13:41.097 --> 00:13:42.576
That's so cute.

128
00:13:43.466 --> 00:13:45.535
He never asks for anything.

129
00:13:45.635 --> 00:13:47.615
- He's your brother.
- Yeah, I know that.


130
00:13:48.872 --> 00:13:52.786
It's like a different planet back there,
you know?


131
00:13:53.376 --> 00:13:57.017
And how do you know?
You haven't been back for ages.


132
00:13:59.015 --> 00:14:00.050
Go.

133
00:14:01.251 --> 00:14:03.492
Yeah, it's been eight years.

134
00:14:05.455 --> 00:14:06.695
You wanna come with me?

135
00:14:08.758 --> 00:14:13.036
Can you please just go meet your brother
so I can finish fixing this place up?


136
00:14:15.231 --> 00:14:17.438
No. Not a chance.

137
00:15:49.459 --> 00:15:50.529
Hey.

138
00:16:03.640 --> 00:16:04.880
You look good.

139
00:16:05.375 --> 00:16:07.013
- Yeah?
- Yeah.


140
00:16:08.945 --> 00:16:10.747
- Yeah...
- No. Really, you look good.


141
00:16:10.847 --> 00:16:13.123
I got a haircut.

142
00:16:14.150 --> 00:16:17.893
Yeah? Yeah, I can see that.

143
00:16:22.392 --> 00:16:25.339
That's Eric. That's Eric.

144
00:16:25.562 --> 00:16:27.599
He's my bestest friend.

145
00:16:29.833 --> 00:16:30.903
Yeah.

146
00:16:32.102 --> 00:16:33.581
Hey, Jakey.

147
00:16:38.875 --> 00:16:42.118
Like Pop had Joe, I have Eric.

148
00:16:44.380 --> 00:16:45.825
Welcome home, kid.

149
00:16:47.884 --> 00:16:49.261
Well, let's go.

150
00:16:50.620 --> 00:16:53.556
- Hey, Jake, will you tell me...
- What?


151
00:16:53.656 --> 00:16:54.964
Where'd it go?

152
00:16:55.191 --> 00:16:57.560
Yeah, will you tell me
how this sounds real fast?


153
00:16:57.660 --> 00:17:00.096
- Yeah, yeah. Sure.
- Listen.


154
00:17:00.196 --> 00:17:05.009
Ladies and gentlemen, I won't take long.
It's the best day of my life.


155
00:17:08.371 --> 00:17:10.112
What is it?

156
00:17:10.874 --> 00:17:12.410
It's a speech, dummy.

157
00:17:13.042 --> 00:17:15.578
- For your wedding. It's a wedding speech.
- Of course.


158
00:17:15.678 --> 00:17:17.080
Of course, it's a wedding speech, yeah.

159
00:17:17.180 --> 00:17:20.218
- Well, is it good?
- Yeah, well, let me hear the rest of it.


160
00:17:22.018 --> 00:17:23.964
That's all I got so far.

161
00:17:24.787 --> 00:17:26.824
It's only seven seconds.

162
00:17:30.360 --> 00:17:32.462
What am I gonna do, Jakey?

163
00:17:32.562 --> 00:17:36.199
Why don't you tell 'em a story?
Like, about when we were kids?


164
00:17:36.299 --> 00:17:38.268
A lot of good stories
from when we were kids.


165
00:17:38.368 --> 00:17:39.402
Yeah, you know, I know!

166
00:17:39.502 --> 00:17:41.538
You know, I'll tell them
about the time that I jumped in the pool


167
00:17:41.638 --> 00:17:43.373
and I broke your Lincoln Log house

168
00:17:43.473 --> 00:17:45.408
- and you were crying like a little girl.
- Yeah!


169
00:17:45.508 --> 00:17:47.610
- You remember that?
- Yeah, right. Yeah, I remember that, yeah.


170
00:17:47.710 --> 00:17:49.679
You took those logs,
I didn't see them for weeks.


171
00:17:49.779 --> 00:17:53.283
- Yeah.
- You said you were gonna fix that house.


172
00:17:53.383 --> 00:17:55.488
Yeah, I did fix it, though, didn't I?

173
00:17:55.985 --> 00:17:57.726
- You did, yeah.
- Didn't I?


174
00:17:59.189 --> 00:18:01.294
Yeah, Buds. You did.

175
00:18:03.092 --> 00:18:04.994
Yeah, that's a great story, Jakey.

176
00:18:05.094 --> 00:18:06.937
- Yeah.
- Yeah.


177
00:18:07.630 --> 00:18:10.042
Yeah, they'll go bananas for that one.

178
00:18:15.605 --> 00:18:17.907
Hey, Jakey,
how many kids you planning on having?


179
00:18:18.007 --> 00:18:20.310
I don't know, Buds. 
That's a ways off.

180
00:18:20.410 --> 00:18:23.012
You know, I'm gonna quit my job
and look after them kids.


181
00:18:23.112 --> 00:18:24.489
Yeah, sure thing, Buds.

182
00:18:25.481 --> 00:18:28.223
- Where are we going?
- It's a surprise.


183
00:18:29.419 --> 00:18:30.787
You got to do
me a favor one second.

184
00:18:30.887 --> 00:18:33.527
- Yeah, I'll do anything.
- You got to close your eyes.


185
00:18:34.023 --> 00:18:36.299
- Really?
- Yeah. Close your eyes.


186
00:18:36.693 --> 00:18:38.128
You want a surprise, or not? Close 'em.

187
00:18:38.228 --> 00:18:39.832
- All right, all right, all right.
- Come on!


188
00:18:42.131 --> 00:18:43.667
Okay, open 'em!

189
00:18:53.977 --> 00:18:55.183
Buds,

190
00:18:56.779 --> 00:18:58.258
what is this?

191
00:19:00.383 --> 00:19:03.193
A promise is a promise, Jakey.

192
00:19:06.289 --> 00:19:08.997
Well, how do you like your wedding gift?

193
00:19:13.329 --> 00:19:14.569
Come on.

194
00:19:17.667 --> 00:19:20.470
Hey, this is my room. 
Right in here.

195
00:19:20.570 --> 00:19:24.040
And your room's over here.
Let me show it to you. Come here.


196
00:19:24.641 --> 00:19:27.577
Buds, where did you get
all the money for this?


197
00:19:27.677 --> 00:19:31.682
I've been working real hard, Jakey.

198
00:19:33.049 --> 00:19:34.392
Real hard.

199
00:19:35.785 --> 00:19:38.955
You know, my boss,
he saves my money up good.


200
00:19:39.055 --> 00:19:42.692
When I told him I was quitting my job
to look after your kids,


201
00:19:42.792 --> 00:19:45.068
you should have seen his face.

202
00:19:45.662 --> 00:19:46.732
He looked...

203
00:19:49.032 --> 00:19:50.978
You still work at the theater, right?

204
00:19:51.968 --> 00:19:54.073
Yeah. Yeah.

205
00:19:55.471 --> 00:19:57.574
Hey, you know
what the best part about that is?


206
00:19:57.674 --> 00:20:00.280
I get to see
all the movies for free.

207
00:20:00.476 --> 00:20:01.678
I tell you that before?

208
00:20:01.778 --> 00:20:05.123
I'm sure gonna miss that. Come here.
I'm gonna put this in your room.


209
00:20:06.449 --> 00:20:10.659
See, Jakey, you get the best room
'cause you're the youngest.


210
00:20:43.653 --> 00:20:45.462
- Hey.
- Hey.


211
00:20:46.122 --> 00:20:47.123
Yeah?

212
00:20:47.223 --> 00:20:48.930
- Yeah.
- Yeah.


213
00:20:49.892 --> 00:20:52.362
- Look at that.
- Yeah, my boss got it for me.


214
00:20:52.462 --> 00:20:53.998
You know, for your wedding.

215
00:20:54.831 --> 00:20:58.901
Yeah, you know, he told the tailor...

216
00:20:59.001 --> 00:21:01.982
- Your boss goes with you to the tailor, Buds?
- No, dummy, no.


217
00:21:02.105 --> 00:21:04.278
The tailor comes to him.

218
00:21:06.109 --> 00:21:08.911
Listen. You know, he told the tailor

219
00:21:09.011 --> 00:21:11.814
that if I wasn't the bestest-looking man
at your wedding,


220
00:21:11.914 --> 00:21:13.518
there'd be a lot of trouble.

221
00:21:14.684 --> 00:21:15.958
A lot of trouble.

222
00:21:19.756 --> 00:21:20.996
He was just kidding.

223
00:21:21.391 --> 00:21:23.526
- No, I know. I know.
- That was a joke.


224
00:21:23.626 --> 00:21:26.664
He seems like a really, really nice man.

225
00:21:27.096 --> 00:21:30.133
- Yeah.
- When do you think I can meet him?


226
00:21:30.233 --> 00:21:32.001
Tomorrow.

227
00:21:32.101 --> 00:21:33.970
Yeah, you know,
he said that after church


228
00:21:34.070 --> 00:21:36.673
that he's gonna take us out to dinner
at El Cortez,


229
00:21:36.773 --> 00:21:38.878
just like Pop used to, remember?

230
00:21:39.308 --> 00:21:40.753
- Yeah.
- Yeah.


231
00:21:43.146 --> 00:21:44.352
Great.

232
00:21:45.548 --> 00:21:48.154
Buds, you think
I could take your car for a drive?


233
00:21:50.153 --> 00:21:52.030
Right now? Yeah.

234
00:21:52.989 --> 00:21:54.093
Here.

235
00:21:56.092 --> 00:21:59.335
- Just don't take long, okay? Please.
- I won't, I won't.


236
00:23:01.190 --> 00:23:02.464
Ignacio?

237
00:23:21.911 --> 00:23:23.185
Ignacio?

238
00:23:32.088 --> 00:23:33.726
Jakey Heckum!

239
00:23:36.092 --> 00:23:38.902
Jakey! Jakey Heckum!

240
00:23:41.230 --> 00:23:45.076
Why did you come back, Jakey?
Why did you...


241
00:23:48.204 --> 00:23:49.615
Go away, Jakey.

242
00:23:50.406 --> 00:23:53.615
What happened? 
What happened to you?

243
00:23:57.480 --> 00:23:59.653
I saved my hands, Jakey.

244
00:24:01.417 --> 00:24:04.296
I saved my hands
so I could still play.

245
00:24:04.954 --> 00:24:06.627
But the music...

246
00:24:07.890 --> 00:24:10.427
The music's gone, Jakey.

247
00:24:12.228 --> 00:24:14.597
The music just stopped.

248
00:24:14.697 --> 00:24:18.235
The fire's the only thing I hear.

249
00:24:18.367 --> 00:24:21.246
And the animal is scared of fire.

250
00:24:22.038 --> 00:24:23.745
Who is scared of fire?

251
00:24:25.741 --> 00:24:28.381
Hench is scared of fire.

252
00:24:30.313 --> 00:24:33.590
What's going on here, Ignacio?
What happened?


253
00:24:36.352 --> 00:24:37.831
Two legs

254
00:24:40.222 --> 00:24:43.066
