01:15:05.712 --> 01:15:06.850
Yeah.

788
01:15:10.083 --> 01:15:13.724
'B's and 'D's, they used to confuse me.

789
01:15:14.520 --> 01:15:17.729
I know. I mix
them up all the time.

790
01:15:18.057 --> 01:15:19.229
Yeah?

791
01:15:23.363 --> 01:15:24.808
You kept it?

792
01:15:27.367 --> 01:15:28.903
All these years?

793
01:15:31.604 --> 01:15:33.049
Yeah, Buds.

794
01:15:35.541 --> 01:15:36.679
Yeah?

795
01:15:39.779 --> 01:15:43.727
Why? Why? It's just six bucks.

796
01:15:44.417 --> 01:15:47.754
It means more to him
than anything in the world.


797
01:15:47.854 --> 01:15:51.961
Because when you got your first paycheck,
you thought of your little brother.


798
01:15:52.959 --> 01:15:55.735
Your brother needs you
to be his best man.


799
01:15:56.596 --> 01:15:59.440
You think this dummy will marry me
without your wedding speech?


800
01:16:14.947 --> 01:16:16.290
Hey, Vee.

801
01:16:19.619 --> 01:16:20.825
Are...

802
01:16:21.954 --> 01:16:24.161
Are there any movie theaters in Verona?

803
01:16:26.059 --> 01:16:28.198
- Yes, Buddy.
- Yeah?


804
01:16:28.628 --> 01:16:29.663
Seven.

805
01:16:30.430 --> 01:16:32.910
Seven? That's a lot.

806
01:16:41.374 --> 01:16:44.446
Well, I need to go get my tuxedo.

807
01:16:45.311 --> 01:16:48.451
I can't leave without my tux. Okay?

808
01:16:49.782 --> 01:16:53.924
All right, you guys eat. Okay?
Just save that for me. I'll be right back.


809
01:16:54.420 --> 01:16:55.421
All right?

810
01:17:03.463 --> 01:17:05.238
I'll be right back!

811
01:17:39.766 --> 01:17:42.301
I hear we're going to war.

812
01:17:42.401 --> 01:17:44.745
Is Franco calling you from hell?

813
01:17:45.705 --> 01:17:47.480
Franco wasn't my man.

814
01:17:48.808 --> 01:17:50.412
Well, then, who?

815
01:17:51.010 --> 01:17:52.945
What will the answer get me?

816
01:17:53.045 --> 01:17:56.822
My word, no war. 
Just tell me who it is.

817
01:17:57.984 --> 01:17:59.725
He's the man who killed Eric.

818
01:18:00.419 --> 01:18:03.366
No, that was your man.
McBradden told me that.


819
01:18:04.791 --> 01:18:08.102
My man, from your side of the fence.

820
01:18:09.428 --> 01:18:11.965
Just tell me the fuckin' name!

821
01:18:12.431 --> 01:18:16.902
I am sorry, Mr. Hench.
I gave him my word.


822
01:18:17.136 --> 01:18:19.412
I promised the young reporter

823
01:18:20.173 --> 01:18:23.484
I would not utter his name.

824
01:18:29.048 --> 01:18:31.187
The fucking vegetarian!

825
01:19:06.886 --> 01:19:08.832
Carry me over the threshold.

826
01:19:29.275 --> 01:19:30.618
Good boy.

827
01:20:08.047 --> 01:20:10.027
Where's college boy at?

828
01:20:12.952 --> 01:20:16.832
Why, it's a secret, Julius.
It's a surprise.


829
01:20:18.891 --> 01:20:23.499
Well, I got a
secret for you, too, Bud.

830
01:20:26.699 --> 01:20:30.738
You see, Garza didn't kill Eric.

831
01:20:32.705 --> 01:20:34.480
But I know who did.

832
01:20:35.174 --> 01:20:36.710
Open that up.

833
01:20:43.015 --> 01:20:44.722
Who is it, Julius?

834
01:20:47.420 --> 01:20:48.694
Tell me.

835
01:20:50.523 --> 01:20:52.799
I'll put a bullet in his head.

836
01:20:54.760 --> 01:20:56.262
I'll kill him.

837
01:20:57.330 --> 01:20:59.401
And then I'll wake him up.

838
01:21:00.499 --> 01:21:03.173
And I'll kill him again.

839
01:21:18.384 --> 01:21:22.188
Jacob wasn't playing
checkers with you that night.


840
01:21:22.288 --> 01:21:23.733
Was he, Bud?

841
01:21:30.096 --> 01:21:31.200
No.

842
01:21:32.231 --> 01:21:33.335
No.

843
01:21:37.136 --> 01:21:41.744
No, hey. Hey, hey.
It wasn't Jake's fault. He...


844
01:21:42.775 --> 01:21:45.415
Poor Jake, he got sick. You know?

845
01:21:46.112 --> 01:21:49.093
Hey, hey. Light me a cigar.

846
01:21:56.088 --> 01:21:58.364
Light me one of those up, son.

847
01:22:09.869 --> 01:22:11.746
Your first horse.

848
01:22:14.206 --> 01:22:15.549
Remember?

849
01:22:17.043 --> 01:22:18.750
We went to Marsha's ranch.

850
01:22:19.645 --> 01:22:22.182
What color was that foal you picked?

851
01:22:30.823 --> 01:22:32.029
It was white.

852
01:22:32.892 --> 01:22:34.064
Right.

853
01:22:36.529 --> 01:22:37.872
For Jake.

854
01:22:39.732 --> 01:22:42.440
Jake never came. Never.

855
01:22:45.538 --> 01:22:48.883
While you waited,
what did we do with that young stallion?


856
01:22:52.478 --> 01:22:54.014
We broke him.

857
01:22:54.246 --> 01:22:55.953
Yes, we broke him.

858
01:23:00.853 --> 01:23:02.196
Sit down!

859
01:23:03.556 --> 01:23:06.926
We got him a saddle.
A gorgeous one, tanned leather.


860
01:23:07.026 --> 01:23:10.337
- Red. Remember that?
- Yeah.


861
01:23:15.801 --> 01:23:18.179
Then what happened to that horse?

862
01:23:20.539 --> 01:23:22.018
A fox bit him.

863
01:23:22.942 --> 01:23:24.478
He got rabies.

864
01:23:25.211 --> 01:23:30.160
That's right, he started kicking and biting,
and that broken horse went crazy.


865
01:23:30.416 --> 01:23:34.592
He could've killed us, son.
What did Pop tell you to do?


866
01:23:36.122 --> 01:23:38.898
That we had to put him to sleep.

867
01:23:39.158 --> 01:23:41.365
And who had to do it?

868
01:23:42.428 --> 01:23:44.066
Me.

869
01:23:44.396 --> 01:23:47.502
Because I loved him the most.

870
01:23:47.633 --> 01:23:52.139
Anyone else, it would've been
too goddamn painful for that horse.


871
01:23:53.806 --> 01:23:56.446
He didn't see that gun in your hand,
your finger on that trigger.


872
01:23:56.675 --> 01:23:59.311
All he saw was your eyes,

873
01:23:59.411 --> 01:24:04.087
your caring, loving eyes,
putting him to sleep.


874
01:24:06.886 --> 01:24:10.561
The last thing that horse felt, Bud.

875
01:24:11.857 --> 01:24:13.200
Your love.

876
01:24:17.997 --> 01:24:20.136
'Cause the horse wasn't bad.

877
01:24:21.967 --> 01:24:23.412
He was just sick.

878
01:24:24.103 --> 01:24:25.241
Yes.

879
01:24:29.108 --> 01:24:31.179
That's what happened with Jake.

880
01:24:31.810 --> 01:24:37.149
The city bit him like a fox. He went mad,
he went insane. He killed Eric.


881
01:24:37.249 --> 01:24:41.425
He made a deal
with Garza to kill me.

882
01:24:43.756 --> 01:24:45.292
Hey, hey, hey.

883
01:24:46.025 --> 01:24:48.164
Hey, no, it ain't his fault.

884
01:24:49.328 --> 01:24:51.934
You see, he got sick.

885
01:24:52.631 --> 01:24:54.577
He just got sick, is all.

886
01:25:06.312 --> 01:25:08.883
You've got to put him to sleep.

887
01:25:10.082 --> 01:25:11.618
At his ranch.

888
01:25:12.985 --> 01:25:15.693
You can visit him there every day.

889
01:25:17.690 --> 01:25:19.931
He will never leave you again.

890
01:25:20.793 --> 01:25:21.999
Never.

891
01:25:25.431 --> 01:25:27.638
This is your final test.

892
01:25:31.203 --> 01:25:33.046
You pass this test,

893
01:25:35.207 --> 01:25:36.811
you will have earned it.

894
01:25:41.513 --> 01:25:42.685
Let's see it.

895
01:25:59.665 --> 01:26:01.110
Look at you.

896
01:26:01.600 --> 01:26:02.874
My son.

897
01:26:06.939 --> 01:26:08.350
Come here.

898
01:26:14.680 --> 01:26:16.284
William Heckum.

899
01:26:18.651 --> 01:26:21.325
The brave son of a proud father

900
01:26:24.556 --> 01:26:26.900
who will put Jake to sleep,

901
01:26:27.593 --> 01:26:29.539
'cause he loves him the most.

902
01:26:32.031 --> 01:26:33.840
You understand, son?

903
01:26:36.201 --> 01:26:37.339
Yeah.

904
01:26:39.204 --> 01:26:40.979
I understand.

905
01:28:36.388 --> 01:28:39.028
Pop said, "Jakey,

906
01:28:39.858 --> 01:28:42.628
"you came into this world after Buddy.

907
01:28:42.728 --> 01:28:46.505
"But he doesn't understand what he's doing,
so you gotta be the big brother."


908
01:28:47.599 --> 01:28:51.012
The next day,
Jakey let me win at checkers


909
01:28:51.203 --> 01:28:53.183
and never beat me again.

910
01:28:54.373 --> 01:28:58.377
And once, you know, when kids at school
called me a slowpoke behind my back,


911
01:28:58.477 --> 01:29:00.047
Jakey got into a fight with them.

912
01:29:00.212 --> 01:29:02.249
He got beat up pretty bad.

913
01:29:03.348 --> 01:29:07.296
But when Mama asked him who done it,
Jakey wouldn't tell.


914
01:29:08.754 --> 01:29:10.789
Pop said, "You know, Jakey's right
to keep it a secret.


915
01:29:10.889 --> 01:29:13.559
"If Buddy found out,
he'd put those boys in the hospital.


916
01:29:13.659 --> 01:29:16.401
"Buddy'd go nuts if anybody hurt Jakey."

917
01:29:18.063 --> 01:29:22.011
And then he told Mama,
"My heart's at peace today.


918
01:29:22.901 --> 01:29:25.938
"'Cause I know when you
and I are no longer on this Earth,


919
01:29:26.038 --> 01:29:28.211
"our boys are gonna
look after each other."


920
01:29:30.776 --> 01:29:32.050
Buds?

921
01:30:13.151 --> 01:30:15.563
Don't splash. Okay? Don't splash.

922
01:30:15.787 --> 01:30:16.822
Aren't you coming, Buds?

923
01:30:16.922 --> 01:30:18.824
Yeah, I'm coming.
I gotta talk to Julius first.


924
01:30:18.924 --> 01:30:19.958
I'm not gonna go without you.

925
01:30:20.058 --> 01:30:21.503
You gotta go, Jakey.

926
01:30:21.660 --> 01:30:23.037
You gotta take care of Vee.

927
01:30:23.562 --> 01:30:26.236
I'm coming, I promise.
I'll be there at your wedding.


928
01:30:44.082 --> 01:30:46.119
What's the grin for, Bud?

929
01:30:49.955 --> 01:30:51.628
I saved the fish.

930
01:30:52.791 --> 01:30:54.293
It swam away.

931
01:30:57.829 --> 01:30:59.365
Jacob's gone.

932
01:31:07.839 --> 01:31:09.409
My pop said

933
01:31:11.510 --> 01:31:13.888
that I'll look after my brother.

934
01:31:15.314 --> 01:31:17.385
Never let anyone hurt him.

935
01:31:22.955 --> 01:31:25.265
Put your hands above your head.

936
01:31:36.969 --> 01:31:39.074
I have to go back for my brother.

937
01:31:44.543 --> 01:31:47.319
We'll find Jake
before the night is over.


938
01:31:48.814 --> 01:31:51.693
And I'll lay him to rest
right next to you.


939
01:31:55.988 --> 01:31:58.093
You'll be together forever.

940
01:32:01.727 --> 01:32:03.764
Just like my wife and son.

941
01:32:05.831 --> 01:32:08.437
Every Sunday I'll put flowers on you.

942
01:32:09.735 --> 01:32:13.046
Red flowers, white flowers.

943
01:32:14.840 --> 01:32:16.513
It'll be perfect.

944
01:32:19.444 --> 01:32:23.893
But right now,
I've got to put you to sleep myself.


945
01:32:25.817 --> 01:32:27.922
Because I love you the most.

946
01:32:30.122 --> 01:32:32.068
You understand me, son?

947
01:32:36.828 --> 01:32:39.104
Yeah, I understand.

948
01:32:40.165 --> 01:32:42.509
I am not your son.

949
01:32:43.101 --> 01:32:45.206
You are not my pop.

950
01:32:46.038 --> 01:32:47.540
You are a bad man.

951
01:33:51.269 --> 01:33:54.341
Now, let me tell
you a story about Vee.

952
01:33:55.307 --> 01:33:57.014
I really like Vee.

953
01:33:58.744 --> 01:34:02.191
I liked her the very second
she spelled her name for me.


954
01:34:03.014 --> 01:34:05.290
I decided right there and then

955
01:34:05.650 --> 01:34:08.597
that I'm gonna
be the best man in her wedding.


956
01:34:10.188 --> 01:34:14.466
And when she and Jakey kiss each other,
I'll clap the loudest.


957
01:34:18.029 --> 01:34:20.198
And as she gets down the altar,

958
01:34:20.298 --> 01:34:22.403
I'll throw flowers on her.

959
01:34:25.871 --> 01:34:30.411
And when she and my brother Jakey
leave the church as a married couple,


960
01:34:32.277 --> 01:34:33.915
I'll go bananas.

961
01:34:39.918 --> 01:34:41.158
Bananas.

962
01:34:44.956 --> 01:34:46.936
And that's all I have to say.